<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Unable to Make Lump Sum Debt Repayments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Russia is unable to repay all
its debts to the people at once due to the flagging consumer
market, Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Yuri Maslyukov said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The state cannot pay off all its debts at one time. Such a
move will cause the collapse of the commodities system," the
Itar-Tass news agency quoted Maslyukov as saying.
</P>
<P>
He also said "the ministries of economy and finance must decide
on the problem of mutual debts between enterprises in the coming
days."
</P>
<P>
Maslyukov called for a tax reform, noting that it is essential
for guaranteeing the interests of Russian citizens, not
corporations or oligarchs.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that the restoration of Russia's money
supply depended on "normalization of companies' current assets,
the arrangement of a normal investment process, and restoration of
the real estate sector."
</P>
<P>
Maslyukov stressed that the current top priority is to
normalize the investment process by imposing strict controls over
the destination of the money, which will help to restore
companies' current assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
