<HEADLINE> Thompson Sets World Short-course Records in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- American Jenny Thompson has
broken her won world short-course record in the 100-meter
butterfly at the FINA Swimming World Cup in College Station of
Texas, the United States.
</P>
<P>
She beat her old mark of 57.79 seconds in the 100m butterfly
with a new world record of 56.90 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
She also won later the 50m freestyle with a time of 24.56 and
beat her U.S. record of 24.78. 
</P>
