<HEADLINE> UK Wants a Joint Defense Agreement With France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Britain and France on Wednesday
are scheduled to agree a defense pact which could help give the
European Union (EU) a voice in military affairs for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook and Defense Secretary George
Robertson are in Paris on Wednesday to meet their French
counterparts, Foreign Minister, Hubert Vedrine and Defense
Minister, Alain Richard.
</P>
<P>
The four leaders were expected to work out details of the
proposed pact, which would broaden already wide foreign and
defense policy cooperation between two of the most powerful EU
states.
</P>
<P>
Their talks will form part of the preparations for the
British-French summit on 3-4 December.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Tony Blair would discuss the proposed pact with
French President Jacques Chirac at the summit this week at the
northern French resort of St Malo.  
</P>
