<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 70 Killed by Cold Spell in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Over 70 people have died during
the cold spell which has affected Poland for the past 15 days,
said Polish police.
</P>
<P>
During the past two weeks, Poland suffered one of the coldest
Novembers in this century, with the lowest temperature hitting
16.9 degrees Centigrade below zero on November 22.
</P>
<P>
The average temperature this November dropped to 2 degrees
Centigrade below zero, compared with 3.2 degrees Centigrade in
previous years.
</P>
<P>
Half of those people who died from the cold weather were
homeless. They froze to death while sleeping on the streets after
drinking, or died from the lack of warm clothing and food, which
is essential for fighting the cold, said the police.
</P>
<P>
Poland now has 500,000 homeless. The government is trying to
take measures to help them get through the cold weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
