<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish DSP Leader Assigned to Form New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel Wednesday appointed Bulent Ecevit, leader of the
center-left Democratic Left Party (DSP), to form a new government.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit, deputy prime minister of the ousted 55th coalition
government, made the announcement following his 40-minute-long
meeting with Demirel at the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
The 55th minority government led by Prime Minister Mesut
Yilmaz collpased after it lost a confidence vote at the 550-seat
parliament on November 25.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Islamic Virtue Party (FP), the True Path Party (DYP) and
the Republican People's Party (CHP), made three motions against
Yilmaz, accusing him of interfering in the privatation plan of a
Turkish Trade Bank and having links with gangs and mafia.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish constitution requires a designated prime minsiter
to form a new government within 45 days.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Demirel, Ecevit told reporters that "I will
spare no efforts to form the new government."
</P>
<P>
He said that he will hold a meeting of the DSP, the fourth
biggest party in the parliament, on Thursday to discuss the
formation of the new cabinet and will touch base with other party
leaders to drum up support for a broad-based government.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit served as primr minister for three times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
