<HEADLINE> WFP Agrees to Give Ethiopia $94.8M in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program
(WFP) and the Ethiopian government signed a five-year country
program agreement here Wednesday worth 94.8 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the Ministry of Economic Cooperation
and Development of Ethiopia said the country program is designed
to support the development activities in line with food security,
education and health sector development.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the WFP will provide 215,817 tons of food
assistance valued at 90.2 million Dollars and the remaining 4.6
million Dollars is in cash funding for training, technical as
well as monitoring and evaluation support.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government will allocate 27.8 million Dollars to
meet the necessary staffing and administrative costs for the
activities, according to the press release.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the governments of Ethiopia and Greece signed a
memorandum of understanding on the supply of 4,000 tons of wheat
worth 1.3 million Dollars in Addis Ababa Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the agreement is to assist Ethiopia in
reducing its food gap and provide budgetary support through the
sale of wheat, according to a press release.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, a grant agreement worth 357,000 Dollars was also
signed here Wednesday between Ethiopia and Austria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
