<HEADLINE> S. African Banks Lower Interest Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's major
commercial banks, ABSA, Standard Bank, First National Bank and
Nedbank announced Wednesday that they will cut their prime
lending rates by a half percentage point to 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
ABSA also announced a 0.5-percentage-point cut in its mortgage
rate to 22.5 percent, South African television, SABC, reported.
</P>
<P>
The rate cut, the third round in as many months, followed a decline
of 23 basis point of the Reserve Bank's repo rate to 19.48 percent.
</P>
<P>
A financial crisis since late May had driven the interest
rates sky-high, dashing hopes of any meaningful economic growth.
</P>
