<HEADLINE> Lake Voctoria Management Coalition Formed in East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- An east African community
organization for better management of Lake Victoria resources was
formed Wednesday in Uganda's second largest city of Jinja, 80 km
east of the capital Kampala.
</P>
<P>
The coalition, formed at the first meeting of the east African
non-governmental organization forum for the lake management, is
to foster proper management of the lake resources and it will
operate through the various shareholders at the community level
in the three countries, namely Uganda, Kenya and Tanzania, the
Uganda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Its formation follows the deteriorating environmental
conditions of the lake basin which have led to growing concern in
the region and the international community at large.
</P>
<P>
The report said the situation in the basin affects both the
land-based and lake-based sources of livelihood, so it requires
concerted efforts from all the three governments and the
community organizations in the region.
</P>
<P>
A total of 28 organizations in the region were represented at
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The participants also decided to establish a task force to
deal with water hyacinth management and promote resource
utilization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
