<HEADLINE> Israel Threatens to Stop Troop Withdrawal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Israel on Wednesday
threatened to suspend the implementation of the Wye peace accord
signed with the Palestinians in Washington in October after an
Israeli solider was attacked in Ramallah.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister's Office said in a statement that if the
Palestinian side could not control the violence against Israelis
in the territories, the Israeli side will stop implementing the
Wye peace accord.
</P>
<P>
This was the strong reaction from the Israeli side towards the
incident in which an Israeli solider was attacked by Palestinian
demonstrators in Ramallah Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said there will be no further Israeli troop
withdrawal from the West Bank until the Palestinian side meets
certain Israeli demands, including publicly announces that it
will not declare an independent Palestinian state next May.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Palestinian university students attacked the Israeli
soldier, Assaf Miara, in Ramallah and then torched the car he was
riding on.
</P>
<P>
Captured by cameras, this incident was shown over and over
again on Israeli televisions, making some wonder whether the
Palestinian security apparatus was trying to control violence in
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The incident began when about 150 students from the Bir Zeit
University, north of Ramallah, were sent to the center of
Ramallah by bus to protest what they called Israeli violation of
Wye agreement.
</P>
<P>
Organized by various political factions, the students staged a
march seeking the release of Palestinian prisoners in Israeli
jails, then walked to a traffic circle, north of Ramallah, and
began stoning Israeli cars.
</P>
<P>
Miara was badly beaten by the students and hospitalized for
head injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
