<HEADLINE> HK Launches 1st On-line Bilingual News Clippings Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- WiseNews, Hong Kong's first
on-line bilingual news clippings service designed specifically to
meet the needs of local customers, was launched here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This innovative scheme was launched by Wisers Information
Limited, one of the pioneering commercial organizations under the
Chinese University of Hong Kong Foundation.
</P>
<P>
It uses two advanced technologies developed by the university,
Information Processing on Chinese and Electronics News Media and
Publishing System, to provide a new level of full text searching
and automatic indexing of English and Chinese language newspapers
and media in Hong Kong, to offer quick and easy access to the
latest news and archives.
</P>
<P>
WiseNews is the first personalized intelligence system of its
kind providing instantaneous full text multilingual search
capability, for information tracking, archive searches,
categorizing and indexing according to priority.
</P>
<P>
Being electronic-based, WiseNews allows information to be
viewed by a far greater number of readers than traditional
paper-based clippings.
</P>
<P>
Professor Arthur K.C. Li, vice-chancellor of the Chinese
University of Hong Kong, said that since the Asian economic crisis
hit Hong Kong, the government has allocated increased resources
to develop innovative technology in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Universities have been encouraged to enhance the application of
technology by industrialists and business people.
</P>
<P>
At the frontiers of technology research, he noted that the
contribution that the Chinese University of Hong Kong has made
goes beyond pure research to a leading role in developing and
transferring advanced technology that boosts the productivity and
competitiveness of Hong Kong companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
