<HEADLINE> Indian Train Derails Killing 8, Injuring 42 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were
killed and 42 others injured when 11 bogies of 8029 down
Kurla-Howrah express train derailed near Jalgaon over 1,000 km
southeast of New Delhi Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that five of the derailed bogies
were badly damaged in the accident. Several trains have been
canceled and Mumbai-bound trains were running late following the
derailment.
</P>
<P>
The real cause of the accident was yet to be ascertained, an
official spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
