<HEADLINE> Romania Readjusts 1998 State Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government
Wednesday announced this year's second cut in budget expenditures
in an effort to keep its deficit within limits.
</P>
<P>
By whittling spending down about 26 million U.S. dollars, the
government hopes it can help to contain the deficit within 3.6
percent of the gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Analysts here count the sluggish privatization process of state
enterprises as the main reason for the budget cut, saying it bit
into expected government revenues.
</P>
<P>
In making re-adjustments, spendings in some budget sections
were cut sharply, while some other sections received supplementary
budgets. However, the overall budget expenditure were reduced.
</P>
<P>
A cut of 530 million dollars was expected in the Ministry of
Finance, the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Health and the
Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ministry of National Defense, the Ministry of
Interior Affairs, the Ministry of Education and the Ministry of
Industry and Trade enjoyed a supplementary budget. The Ministry of
National Defense received 233 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Finance Daniel Daianu said the budget cut would not
affect the routine operation of related ministries, adding the cut
was mainly done in investment capital which hasn't been used.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government previously announced a 10 percent
budget cut three months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
