<HEADLINE> Yarlung Zangbo Gorge Expedition Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHAQU(TIBET), December 3 (Xinhua) -- The expedition to the
Yarlung Zangbo Grand Canyon, the world's longest, deepest and
perhaps most dangerous gorge on the Yarlung Zangbo River in
Tibet, ended today.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time anyone successfully traveled through
the gorge on foot. The expedition was completed in 42 days.
</P>
<P>
The 496-kilometer-long canyon has an average depth of 5,000
meters, and is a challenge to any adventurer. Several Chinese and
foreign teams had attempted to go through it in the past, but they
all failed, and in some cases, team members lost their lives.
</P>
<P>
The team that just successfully completed its trek through the
canyon consisted of Chinese scientists, news reporters and athletes,
and faced many hazards along the way, according to sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
