<HEADLINE> Farm Machinery Manufacturer Gains Shenzhen Listing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Feicai Vehicle
Shareholding Company from east China's Anhui Province listed 36
million A-shares today on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange in south
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 24.85 million shares traded today with the per share value
rising by 110 percent and closing at 14 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Analyst noted that the brisk trading indicates the high
investor interest in the country's farm machinery market.
</P>
<P>
Feicai ranks as one of China's top six farm machinery
manufacturers and accounts for 10.64 of the domestic market for
related items.
</P>
<P>
The company produced some 176,500 units in 1997, with profits
for the year standing at 64 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company issued shares valued at 256 million yuan by the end
of September, with related funds earmarked for technological
upgrading and product development.
</P>
<P>
Feicai expects to increase its annual production capacity to
500,000 units and 1.5 million meters of chains for industrial use
by the year 2000, with annual sales expected to reach five billion
yuan. 
</P>
