<HEADLINE> Netanyahu: Palestinians Must Live up to Commitments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 3 (Xinhua)-- Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu said here Thursday Israel will implement the
Wye peace accord only after the Palestinians fulfil their
commitments.
</P>
<P>
''Otherwise, there will be no peace process, " Netanyahu said
to reporters after his meeting with U.S. Secretary of Health Donna
Shalala.
</P>
<P>
He strongly criticized a violent attack against the Israelis
Wednesday in Ramalah, adding such violence was organized by the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
The TV crews were there (in Ramallah) Wednesday not by chance
and everything was well organized, he said.
</P>
<P>
Two Israelis were attacked and beaten by demonstrating
Palestinian students in the Ramallah incident.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, the Israeli government set three
conditions for the Palestinians to fulfil, or it will halt
further Israeli troop withdrawal from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The conditions include the PNA acceptance of continued
imprisonment of Palestinian prisoners with blood on hands, ,
renouncement of its intention to unilaterally declare a
Palestinian state and halt to incitment activities.
</P>
<P>
The PNA said Wednesday night that Israel has no right to raise
more demands in implementing the Wye peace accords and such
demands violated the Wye accord.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. State Department said Wednesday that it is not
appropriate to add new demands and the Wye peace accord must be
implemented as signed.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Clinton is to visit Gaza, but the
Israeli side has asked the President not to land his special plane
at the Arafat International Airport, requesting him to take a
helicopter to reach Gaza.
</P>
<P>
U.S. peace envoy Dennis Ross will return to the Middle East
soon to help implement the Wye peace accord signed in Washington
in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
