<HEADLINE> Chirac Calls for Relentless Fight Against Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Thursday called for a relentless fight against terrorism and
reinforcement of international cooperation in fighting what he
called "terrorist networks."
</P>
<P>
He made the appeal during a ceremony held in the Invalides
military museum to inaugurate a bronze sculpture in memory of the
victims of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
This also fell on the second anniversary of a bombing attack on
a railway train in Paris by Islamic extremists.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that the international community should reinforce
cooperation to "adapt itself to the new reality" that terrorists
have set up networks around the world.
</P>
<P>
The sculpture was a victim of terrorism holding his head in his
hands. 
</P>
