<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Declines in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports fell by 4.8 percent in September 1998 from the same
month last year, and that of domestic exports by 12.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, the volume of total exports decreased by 6.0
percent. Concurrently, the volume of imports dropped by 8.2.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by the volume and price statistics of
external trade for September 1998 released by the Census and
Statistics Department Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first nine months of 1998 with the same period
last year, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports decreased by 1.9
percent, and the volume of domestic exports by 5.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, the volume of total exports decreased by 2.3
percent. Meanwhile, imports fell by 4.8 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing September 1998 with September 1997, the prices of
re-exports and domestic exports fell by 4.9 percent and 3.2
percent respectively. Import prices also declined by 5.7
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
