<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Records Booming Operation in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Both passenger and cargo traffic
via the Macao International Airport rose considerably in November.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 181,677 passengers used the airport in
November, an increase of 24 percent over the same month of last
year.
</P>
<P>
During the first 11 months of the year, passenger traffic grew
by 13 percent over the same months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
In November, cargo traffic reached 6,698 tons, posting an
increase of 16 percent over November 1997. For the 11 months,
cargo growth over 1997 was 45 percent.
</P>
<P>
On December 8 this year, the airport will celebrate the third
anniversary of its official opening. A relevant ceremony will be
held and special souvenirs for passengers on that day will be
distributed.
</P>
<P>
Since its commercial opening on November 9, 1995, the airport
has handled about 5.33 million passengers and 130,000 tons of
cargo.
</P>
<P>
The 13 airline companies using the airport offer 390 weekly
scheduled flights to 25 destinations, 13 of which are on the
mainland areas of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
