<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Sees Steady Population Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Macao's resident population
reached 427,400 by the end of September, up about 5,000 from the
end of last year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Census and Statistics Department made the estimate in
a press release on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the third quarter of the year, 1,191 births and 290
deaths were recorded. The major cause of death was circulation
system illness and tumor.
</P>
<P>
The number of legal immigrants from China's mainland areas
reached 804 between July and September.
</P>
<P>
At the end of September, 55,315 foreign people, including
31,281 laborers coming from outside Macao, had obtained
permissions to live in Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
