<HEADLINE> India Conducting Big-scale Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Following its big-scale
amphibious three-service combine military exercise in its western
coast in mid- November, Indian army and Air Force are conducting
military exercise in its western desert state of Rajasthan near
Indo-Pak border.
</P>
<P>
Starting from November 30, the "mock war" between two
demarcated groups "Red Land" and "Blue Land" of army and Air Force
personnel would continue till December 12, official sources said
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The combat exercise, which is called "Shiv Shakti", involved
over 66,000 officers and soldiers from the two services. Of the
armaments there are 700 air vehicles, 300 tanks, 200 combat
vehicles, missiles in addition to a host of soft propelled and
unarmed vehicles involved in the exercise.
</P>
<P>
"Shiv Shakti" dealt with conduct of operations in desert
atmosphere involving both aerial and land surveillance and
superior contact in logistic infrastructure with wide ranging
application of technology, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The military exercise is being "routinely" conducted every year
and India is "displaying enough transparency " of it, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Western nations and Pakistan in particular have shown great
concern over India's big military exercises along the Indo-Pak
border areas in the past few days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
