<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Further Develop Trade with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Mongolia and
China has developed smoothly and is expected to grow, said a high-
ranking Mongolian official Thursday.
</P>
<P>
R. Amarjargal, acting minister of external relations, told
Xinhua there are no remarkable pending issues in the bilateral
trade, and the signing of all necessary documents on the
development of economic and trade cooperation between the two
countries has laid a foundation for the promotion of bilateral
economic ties.
</P>
