<HEADLINE> New Headway in China's Good-Neighborly Diplomacy This Year (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Xinhua Writers Li Shijia and Yang Guoqiang
</P>
<P>
The visit earlier this year by Pakistan's Prime Minister Mian
Nawaz Sharif also served to consolidate the Sino-Pakistani
cooperative partnership and promote the traditional friendship for
the coming century.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that China has continued to increase ties
with its neighbors by placing importance on regional political and
economic cooperation to ease the Asian financial crisis and
promote regional peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
China also offered to provide 5.5 billion U.S. dollars for some
Asian countries and proposed an Agenda on Science and Technology
Industry Cooperation to APEC for the 21st century and established
a 10-million-U.S.-dollar China-APEC Science and Technology
Industry Cooperation Fund.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, other Chinese leaders will visit
neighboring nations and they include Vice-President Hu Jintao's
trip to Viet Nam and Vice-Premier Li Lanqing's visit to Thailand,
while Mongolia's President N. Bagabandi will visit China from
December 7 to 12.
</P>
<P>
Observers here say that as the the Asian financial crisis
deteriorates, China would join its neighbors in contributing more
to regional peace, stability and development. 
</P>
