LOS ANGELES -- Microsoft founder Bill Gates said Wednesday that
he will donate 100 million U.S. dollars to help vaccinate children
in developing countries, according to reports from the company.
</P>
<P>
"New life-saving vaccines quickly become available to children
in the developed world, but recent history shows us that children
in the developing world have to wait up to 15 years for the same
vaccine," Gates said. This is the second donation in a week that
