<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Insurance Industry Experiences Rapid Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China's insurance industry has
experienced rapid development over the past 20 years and a
complete insurance system has basically been established since
establishment of the China Insurance Regulatory Commission (CIRC)
in November.
</P>
<P>
This year's insurance premiums are expected to grow
significantly over last year's level in spite of a lower economic
growth rate.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China, the central bank, decided to
reinstate the domestic insurance sector in 1980 following a
suspension of some 20 years. with premiums for the first year
amounting to less than 300,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
However, the sector has since risen at an annual average rate
of over 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics through the end of 1997 show that domestic
insurance premiums have exceeded 100 billion yuan, including
property premiums of some 48 billion yuan and life premiums
totalling 60 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The number of domestic insurance companies has jumped from one
in 1978 to the current 13 with total assets worth over
164.6 billion yuan and over 140,000 employees. Four insurance
companies are currently engaged in fierce market competition in
the nation's medium-sized and large cities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Sports Delegation Leaves for 13th Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Four hundred officials and
athletes of the Chinese Sports Delegation Thursday boarded two
