<HEADLINE> A New Political Party Set Up in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- A new political party, United
Party for National Development (UPND), has been set up in Zambia,
Zambia Daily Mail reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The party has listed seven main objectives among which are to
spearhead economic and social development; to harmonize tribal,
racial and gender relations in the country; to promote democratic
practices and values; and to adhere to good and democratic
governance.
</P>
<P>
Other objectives are to ensure the rule of law; to protect
every citizens's fundamental human rights; to protect freedom of
speech and assembly provided it does not impinge on the rights of
others; and to respect freedom of worship.
</P>
<P>
Out-going Anglo American Corporation chief executive for east
and central Africa and presidential aspirant, Anderson Mazoka,
announced the formation of the new party last week, said the
local newspaper. 
</P>
