<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Industry Output Down in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The output of the manufacturing
sectors of the Philippines plummeted year-on-year by 16.4 percent
in September due to plunge in transport equipment and
construction-related sectors, the country's National Statistics
Office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Value of production in the manufacturing sectors decreased by
7.8 percent in September compared with a year earlier, the office
said.
</P>
<P>
Transport equipment fell year-on-year by 53.1 percent in volume
of production and 46.9 percent in value in September, it said.
</P>
<P>
Volume and value of the production of basic metals plunged by
29.5 percent and 21.0 percent respectively in September from a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Chemicals posted a 15-percent drop in volume of production and
a 1.9 percent decline in value of production during the period
while non-metallic mineral products recorded drops of 27.4 percent
in volume and 34.8 percent in value of production.
</P>
<P>
Gainers in both volume and value of production were sectors of
petroleum refineries, food, paper and paper products and beverage.
</P>
<P>
The capacity utilization, defined as the ratio of output to the
maximum producing capacity of a plant, showed that plants
operating below 70 percent of their capacity were 39.4 percent of
the total in September compared with 31.3 percent a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Volume and value of production of the country's manufacturing
sectors declined by 17 percent and 7.6 percent respectively in
August this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
