<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Nepal Up in First 11 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in Nepal by
air reached 360,875 in the first 11 months of this year, up 11.8
percent over the same period of last year, official figures show.
</P>
<P>
During this period, tourist arrivals from other countries
excluding India grew by 12.6 percent to 231,236 while those from
neighboring India were 129,639, up 10.3 percent, according to
figures provided Thursday by the Department of Tourism.
</P>
<P>
Tourist arrivals in Nepal stood at 28,883, 33,145, 53,314 and
 39,911 respectively in August, September, October and November.
</P>
<P>
It seems unlikely that the Himalayan kingdom can achieve its
target of attracting 500,000 tourists during the Visit Nepal Year
'98.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is a major foreign exchange earner for the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
