<HEADLINE> Coffee Prices on Rise in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan coffee prices showed an
upward trend for the second week runing as a 50-kg bag of clean
coffee in premium grades fetched up to present 12,100 Shillings
(201 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the 16,299 bags offered by Coffee Board of Kenya (CBK)
were sold at this week's auction, an increment from last week's
13,305 bags, the East African Standard reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest CBK price catalogue, the highest price
offered was 12,100 Shillings in category AA compared with 10,234
Shillings (170 Dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
Price in the same category ranged from 8,550 Shillings (142
Dollars) to 12,100 Shillings for all the 50-kg bags.
</P>
<P>
In the second category, AB, prices ranged from 8,200 Shillings
(136 Dollars) to 10,776 Shillings (179 Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The lowest price recorded was 1,870 Shillings (31 Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Coffee prices in the east African country have improved
steadily during the past two weeks and competition among dealers
was high at the Nairobi Coffee Exchange, the CBK added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
