<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Coal Sales Plunging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand's total coal
sales in the third quarter this year were down 21 percent on the
same quarter last year, according to Statistics New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
In a media release issued Thursday, deputy government
statistician Ian Ewing said the latest energy statistics showed
sales of sub-bituminous coal were down 27.5 percent because of a
fall in the amount of thermal electricity generated, and sales of
bituminous coal were 21.3 less because of a decline in exports.
</P>
<P>
Electricity generation in the third quarter was 4.2 percent
lower than the same quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
"The flat state of the New Zealand economy may have contributed
to this lower demand for electricity," Ewing said.
</P>
<P>
Hydro generation in New Zealand rose 9.8 percent with high
South Island lake levels compared with 1997 levels. However, this
was more than offset by thermal generation, 27.6 less.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of refined petrol produced during the third
quarter was down 5.3 percent compared with the corresponding
period of last year. Regular petrol refining (91 octane) was 8.4
percent lower, while premium petrol (94 octane) refining was five
percent higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
