<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Take Part in 13th Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar athletes will take part
in the 13th Asian Games scheduled to be held from December 6 to
20 in Bangkok, Thailand.
</P>
<P>
A total of 50 Myanmar athletes will compete in only five
categories which are rowing, sepak takraw, women's weightlifting,
women's taekwondo and women's archery.
</P>
<P>
When meeting here Wednesday with members of the Myanmar sports
contingent taking part in the games, Lieutenant-General Khin
Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council, stressed that the aim of sending them to the games is to
win medals rather than gaining experiences merely as in the past.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also chairman of the Myanmar National
Olympic Council, admitted that camp training was given only to
athletes of 10 categories though Myanmar can take part in 27
sports categories of the 36 to be competed in the games, taking
into consideration of the prospects to win medals.
</P>
<P>
Of the 10 categories, only 50 athletes of five categories, who
have high hopes to win medals, were selected to take part in the
games, he said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar athletes won a total of 190 medals during the last two
years after the Ministry of Sports was established in December
1996 and 63 sports contigents sent abroad for contests since
then. 
