<HEADLINE> IPU Stresses Food Security in Underdeveloped Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-Parliamentary Union
(IPU) Wednesday emphasized the priority of securing food supplies
in underdeveloped countries at a special meeting here.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, jointly organized by the United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO), Italian parliament and IPU, was
aimed at facilitating the attainment, through sustainable
development, of the objectives as set by the World Food Summit of
1997.
</P>
<P>
In the final document of the meeting, the IPU recommended ways
for resolving the world's food supply problems, including
harmonization of relevant laws of different countries, convocation
of a conference on world food security once a year, and
coordination among U.N. organizations.
</P>
<P>
About 270 parliamentarians from 70 countries attended the
four-day meeting, which ended Wednesday. 
</P>
