<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 26 in Manila Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of a big fire,
which struck a settlement house in Paco, Manila, before dawn
Thursday, rose to 26 as two more bodies were found.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest reports, most of the victims are
children abandoned by their parents and more than 10 people are
still missing.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters, volunteer groups and terrified parents were
scouring the debris of the blaze, which leveled the compound of
the Dama de Pilipinas settlement house in Plaza Dilao, Paco around
02:00 (18:00 GMT Wednesday).
</P>
<P>
The settlement house was occupied by a total of 60 people,
including abandoned children, babies left by their working parents
on a day care basis and volunteers who took care of the kids.
</P>
<P>
The affected areas were cottages 1 and 2, pavilion 4 for
yearlings and the area for nursery.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said three children died in cottage 1, which
had 11 occupants, and eight were saved.
</P>
<P>
Cottage 2 was occupied by 22 people, 18 of whom died, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
In the nursery section, all seven occupants were killed and six
others in the yearlings area also died.
</P>
<P>
The survivors were taken to the nearby parish church in Plaza
Dilao.
</P>
<P>
The corpses were transferred to a funeral home along J. Abad
Santos Avenue in Tondo, Manila.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
