<HEADLINE> Moroccan Prime Minister Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of Morocco
Abderrahmane Youssoufi and his party arrived here this morning
for a five-day official visit to China at the invitation of
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi's some 150-member entourage includes his wife, three
cabinet ministers as well as entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu is expected to preside over a welcoming ceremony in
honor of Youssoufi here this afternoon and the two leaders will
hold formal talks following the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Beijing, Youssoufi and his party are scheduled
to visit Qingdao, a coastal city in east China's Shandong
province, and Shanghai, China's largest economic center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
