<HEADLINE> URGENT 24 Filipinos Killed in Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty four people, including 19
abandoned children and five volunteer house parents, were killed
in a fire which struck a settlement house in Paco, Manila, before
dawn Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters, volunteer groups and terrified parents were still
scouring the debris of the blaze which leveled the compound of the
Dama de Pilipinas settlement house in Plaza Dilao, Paco.
</P>
<P>
The settlement house was occupied by a total of 60 people
including abandoned children and babies left by their working
parents on a day-care basis.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at about 02:09 (18:00 GMT Wednesday).
</P>
</TEXT>
