<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA Nods in Agreement with Pan Am Games' Soccer Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- FIFA has approved Winnipeg's
plans for next July's Pan American Games soccer matches in
Winnipeg, Canada.
</P>
<P>
Organizers got FIFA's approval after they promised to improve
their soccer facilities.
</P>
<P>
In earlier this Autumn, FIFA representative Hugo Salceda and
sports delegates from Brazil, Argentina and Uruguay inspected two
stadiums for the Game's soccer match and pointed out that the
sites were lack of permanent seats.
</P>
<P>
Organizers argued that adding permanent seats would severely
damage the playing field but finally they agreed to install
between 2,500 and over 3,000 permanent seats at the Waverley
soccer complex.
</P>
<P>
They also promised to improve an indoor warm-up facility, add
more on-field media positions and enhance lighting for television.
</P>
<P>
The two playing fields were for men's and women's soccer
matches respectively. Initially, organizers only provided one
field for both.
</P>
<P>
5,000 athletes from 42 countries will compete in 41 events in
the XIII Pan American Games from next July 23 to August 8 in
Winnipeg, Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
