<HEADLINE> Tourists to Indonesia Down 19 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreign tourists
coming to Indonesia slumped by about 19 percent to 2.91 million
during the first 10 months of this year, from 3.56 million during
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ministry of Art and Culture on
Wednesday, the lowest level of tourist arrivals was recorded in
May when massive unrest hit Jakarta and forced the resignation of
former Indonesia President Soeharto. Only 226,700 foreign tourists
visited the country during the month.
</P>
<P>
The peak level was recorded in August when tourist arrivals
reached 352,500, national newspapers Thursday quoted the
ministry's report as saying.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange receipts from tourism in the January to
October period were estimated at 2.94 billion U.S. dollars, 19.5
percent less than the 3.65 billion dollars recorded in the same
period last year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The unfavorable political situation in the country has posed a
serious obstacle to tourism development and promotion. This has
prompted the Art and Culture Ministry to take precautionary
measures including the setting up of a crisis center and promotion
through Let's Go Indonesia and Indonesia Spectacular in
association with the national tourism industry, including the
Hotels and Restaurants Association and the Association of
Indonesian Tour and Travel Agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
