<HEADLINE> Ecuador to Host Regional Telecom Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Telecommunications Commission (CITEL) will meet here on December
7-11 to chart the growth of the sector in South and North America.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's National Telecommunications Council President Daniel
Rodriguez said on Wednesday that the meeting is expected to boost
the growth of communications in the region and worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Argentina, Brazil, Canada, Colombia, Ecuador,
the United States, Grenada, Honduras, Mexico and Paraguay are
expected to join the regional event, Rodriguez said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will enable the Ecuadoran authorities to learn from
experiences of other Latin American countries in privatizing and
modernizing the telecommunications sector, Rodriguez said.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador is restructuring and updating its telecom network. But
the government's efforts to sell the state-run telecom operation
or part of its shares failed months ago.
</P>
<P>
The government is now planning to revise the existing laws to
facilitate a privatization program in the first quarter of 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
