<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese Province Reports Fast Growth in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Guizhou Province has had 128
million tourists since the first group of travelers came in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Tourism Administration said that it has earned
7.6 billion yuan (916 million U.S. dollars) from tourism,
including 183 million U.S. dollars from overseas tourist services.
</P>
<P>
Guizhou has unique karst formations and a picturesque landscape
and is home to many ethnic groups with colorful folklore and
customs. The province is also where China's reputedly best neutral
spirits like Maotai are produced.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 220 flights to cities outside Guizhou each
week. It also has 50 hotels that are approved for overseas
tourists, the official said.  
</P>
