Telecommunications and the Iridium Southeast Asia Co. Ltd. of
Thailand also signed a contract under which the Thai company will
provide technical services to the Myanmar side as part of the two
countries' technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Thailand, one of the leading foreign investors in Myanmar,
ranked third after Singapore and Britain in investment with 1.237
billion U.S. dollars in 42 projects out of over 7 billion dollars'
total foreign investment in the country at the end of May this
year.
</P>
<P>
The investment covers such sectors as oil and gas, hotels and
tourism, livestock breeding and fishery, industrial estate and
transport. 
