<HEADLINE> Promoting Cleaner Industrial Production In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Taiyuan, the capital of north
China's Shanxi Province, has been chosen by the United Nation's
Environment Program as the first pilot city in China to try out
clean production techniques.
</P>
<P>
Taiyuan is a major energy and heavy chemicals center and faces
mounting environmental pollution problems.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city government and many large enterprises
like Taiyuan Steel and Iron Company and No. 2 Heat and Power Plant
have taken steps to promote cleaner production and to reduce
pollution.
</P>
<P>
According to city officials and members of the China Committee
for International Environmental and Developmental Cooperation,
Taiyuan will focus on new methods for using coal, urban garbage
burning facilities, and environment-friendly industrial
boilers.
</P>
<P>
It will update its industrial emissions treatment technology,
auto tailpipe emissions, and industrial waste, and study other
clean production technology.
</P>
<P>
Taiyuan is expected to have cleaner production in all
industries by the year 2005, officials say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
