<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- China's "Spring City" of Jinan,
capital of Shandong Province, plans to rename 72 of its best
springs, according to the Best Springs Protection and Management
Office.
</P>
<P>
Jinan is to the north of Taishan Mountain and to the south of
the Yellow River and has 139 springs in urban areas with names.
</P>
<P>
Li Shixin, director of the Jinan Best Springs Protection and
Management Office, explained that people often use the 72 springs
as representative of Jinan, but, they have different names from
different historical periods.
</P>
<P>
Li said that there are at least three names for each of these 72
and the purpose of the renaming program is to standardize their
names. Some springs included in the previous best springs have
dried up, and some that are not included are of great value in
their beauty.  
