<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zhongshan Memorial Hall
in Guangzhou, capital of southern China's Guangdong Province, has
reopened to the public after completion of major renovations.
</P>
<P>
The hall, built in 1931 with donations from Guangzhou residents
and overseas Chinese in memory of the great forerunner of the
Chinese revolution, Sun Yat-sen, is renowned for its artistic
architectural design, and has been the venue for many important
meetings and performance.
</P>
