<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese City Beginning New Tour Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of
Guangdong Province in south China, is to start a new tour program
to help local tourism between December 5 and 30.
</P>
<P>
The "10,000 tourists visiting Guangzhou" program was organized
by the Guangzhou Urban Tourism Administration and has attracted
40-odd travel agencies from Guangdong, Hong Kong, and Macao. It
gives tourists in Guangzhou different types of discounts of as
much as 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has a 2,210-year history but was also an important
modern Chinese revolutionary base. It was one of the earliest
ports of trade with the outside world. The city is on the Pearl
River and has many historical sites.
</P>
<P>
A large party will be held the evening of December 5 to mark the
start of the new tour program, according to the city's tourism
administration.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou had 13.15 million tourists from January to September
and took in 21.58 billion yuan from related services, up 6.1
percent from the same period last year.  
