<HEADLINE> Beijing Records Rapid Increase in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has had an annual
increase of 26 percent in its foreign trade since the reforms and
opening up began two decades ago, according to the municipal
economic and foreign trade commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that imports and exports for the 1979-1997
period totalled 33.07 billion U.S. dollars and the ratio of
exports and imports to the city's GDP went from 4.8 percent in
1978 to 26.5 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xuequn, a commission official, said that great changes
have taken place in the export mix, with finished industrial
products accounting for 92 percent, the highest percentage in the
country. There has also been a marked increase in exports of
electro-mechanical products and high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's commodities are exported to more than 150 countries
and regions, compared with 80 in 1978.  
</P>
</TEXT>
