<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doctor Detects Diseases Through the Eyes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Huang Laowu, a member of the
Zhuang nationality in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, has his own special way of diagnosing diseases --
examining the eyes.
</P>
<P>
By examining changes in the whites of the eyes, Huang claims to
be able to diagnose 238 different diseases, more than 85 percent
of which are verified by ultra-sonic tests.
</P>
<P>
Huang's eye-diagnosis has proved to be especially effective in
detecting diabetes, nephritis, kidney stone and hepatitis.
</P>
<P>
Huang has treated 87 hepatitis patients, all of whom have
completely recovered, except for the two who didn't listen to the
doctor's advice and died from drinking too much liquor.
</P>
<P>
Huang's eye-diagnosis has won support from the state and is
listed in the research programs of regional and state ministries.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
