<HEADLINE> Anhui Province Attracts Taiwan Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province, a major grain
producer at the lower reaches of the Yangtze River, plans to
introduce more investment from Taiwan Province to accelerate local
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
These funds will mainly be directed to hi-tech industries,
along with other major enterprises, in line with the province's
long-term development plan, according to acting governor Wang
Taihua, who said that large projects are especially encouraged.
</P>
<P>
Wang told Xinhua recently that his province is blessed with
rich mineral, water and agricultural resources, a cheap labor
force and sound infrastructure. The province greatly impressed a
group of 60 leading Taiwanese businessmen who visited there last
month, he noted.
</P>
<P>
To date, there are over 700 Taiwanese-funded projects in this
eastern province, with total capital of 880 million
U.S. dollars. Most of these firms were set up in the last six
years.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that an increasing number of Taiwan
industrial giants have settled in Anhui, raising the average
investment for each Taiwanese-funded project from 730,000
U.S. dollars at the beginning of the 1990s to 4.3 million
U.S. dollars last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
