<HEADLINE> U.S. Football Player Sentenced One Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Football defensive
back Tremain Mack was sentenced to 356 days in jail for drunken
driving charge in October.
</P>
<P>
Mack, who plays for Cincinnati Bengals, went to jail today to
complete a 30-day term imposed last year after being arrested in
Clermont County, Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
Municipal Court judge James Shriver ruled that Mack had
violated his probation by getting arrested again on the latest a
drunken driving charge. He order the player to complete portion
of the sentence suspended after he pleaded no contest to drunken
driving.
</P>
<P>
Mack, who was arrested in October. He was charged with drunken
driving, resisting arrest and driving without a license. He is
scheduled for trial on those charges in January. 
</P>
