<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Authorities Concerned with Air Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The General Administration of
Aviation of China, concerned about air safety, has asked local air
transporters to step up safety management in accordance with the
law.
</P>
<P>
Wang Li'an, a deputy director of the administration, told a
recent aviation meeting here that after 1992 and 1993, when a
series of air incidents including hijackings occurred, local civil
aviation companies have strived to achieve greater air safety.
</P>
<P>
However, the air-safety situation today is still unstable due
to certain weaknesses, he said. The deputy director called for the
standardization of safety management at all aviation companies.
</P>
<P>
The aviation meeting participants visited the Xiamen Aviation
Co., Ltd. which has been granted the "Gold Swan Cup," an annual
national award for air safety, for the past three straight years.
</P>
