<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0337 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Black Dog's Hair Turns White When Companion Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 3 (Xinhua) -- A black dog felt so mournful
over the death of its companion, a brown-haired dog, that the hair
on top of its head turned white overnight, according to the
Beijing Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
Xie Chaofu of the city of Duyun in southwest China's Guizhou
Province, the owner of the two dogs, was quoted as saying that the
black dog growled lowly around the corpse of the brown dog and
attacked anybody who tried to approach the dead dog one late
November day.
</P>
<P>
The brown dog, crushed to death by a truck on the street, was
inseparable from the black dog all its life, under the care of Xie.
</P>
<P>
The next day, Xie was startled to discover that the
black-haired dog had a patch of cup-sized white hair on top of its
head. The white hair gradually turned black again after Xie buried
the brown dog.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0338 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong to Import More Advanced Irrigation Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
which produces one-tenth of the country's grain, plans to import
advanced water-saving irrigation equipment from abroad for
use on some one-million hectares of farmland over the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
These imports will include advanced spraying, seeping and
dripping technology, according to an official at the Provincial
Water Conservation Department.
</P>
<P>
Over the next three years, the provincial government will
subsidize 50 million yuan (six million US dollars) in this program
annually, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's per-capita water resource stands at only 357 cubic
meters, 20 cubic meters fewer than that of Israel.
</P>
<P>
Around 1.8 million of the 4.67 million hectares of farmland in
Shandong have been hit with droughts to one degree or another for
the past 48 years, resulting in annual losses of 1.5 billion
kilograms of grain.
</P>
<P>
Since the early 1970s, Shandong province has imported
water-saving irrigation technology from the United States,
France, Italy, Israel and Austria. So far, this advanced equipment
has been used over 2.1 million hectares of local farmland, the
most widespread use of such technology in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981203.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapid Urbanization In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Some people in China's
Zhejiang Province are improving their living conditions by
gradually moving towards an urban lifestyle.
</P>
<P>
The fast development of the industrial and service sectors
brought annual incomes of most farmers in Zhejiang to 3,684 yuan
(444 U.S. dollars)last year, and they are estimated to be nearly
4,000 yuan this year. Most rural people do not have to worry about
how to make ends meet any longer and pay more attention to how to
make their lives more comfortable.
</P>
<P>
People now eat more fish and meat instead of just vegetables
and have an average of 75 grams of protein in their daily diets.
</P>
<P>
They also dressed more or less the same as urbanites,
especially farmers in the more developed cities of Hangzhou,
Wenzhou and Ningbo, and per capita floor space is 37.3 square
meters now, twice the amount of 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Interior decoration has become fashionable in rural areas, with
spending on it up 28.4 percent, and the quality of materials is
improving to include granite, ceramic tiles, carpets, and
wallpaper.
</P>
<P>
Household electrical appliances are no longer a rarity in rural
areas, and air conditioners, vacuum cleaners, video players, and
cameras are increasingly seen to be needs, alongside washing
machines and refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
Rural people are also spending more on telecommunications and
transport, on motorcycles, automobiles, mobile phones and
pagers. Average expenditure on these items is 88.75 yuan per
capita, 52.4 percent up more than for last year.
</P>
<P>
More attention is being paid to health as well, and people have
given up the old idea that illnesses can cure themselves. Average
spending on physical examinations and medical treatment per capita
for the first half of this year was 71.79 yuan, 17.8 percent more
than for the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
