<HEADLINE> China Introduces Giraffes From South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- A couple of African giraffes
settled down in the Changsha Zoo in central-south China's Hunan
Province after a 1,200-kilometer truck ride from Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The couple are among 34 African giraffes China brought into the
country from South Africa in October.
</P>
<P>
The giraffes were reportedly caught in Africa by nets thrown by
over them from helicopters.
</P>
<P>
A zoo official said the two two-year-old giraffes are about
three-meters high and weight about 400 kilograms each. These are
the first giraffes ever in Changsha Zoo.
</P>
<P>
The Changsha Zoo has equipped the giraffe house with heating
installations and is preparing a 1,000-square-meter area for the
giraffes to romp around in outdoors.
</P>
<P>
The other 32 African giraffes were imported by several other
provincial zoos.  
