<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil Prices Close Modestly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Oil markets on Wednesday warmed
to a sharp drawdown in U.S. oil inventories, as the benchmark
Brent traded last at $10.38 a barrel, up 16 cents.
</P>
<P>
The American Petroleum Institute late on Tuesday reported a 5.7
million barrel draw in U.S. crude stocks last week, against market
expectations for a build-up in stocks.
</P>
<P>
"The draw is encouraging, but distillate stocks are still very
high," Mehdi Varzi, director of oil and gas research at Dresdner
Kleinwort Benson in London, was quoted by Reuters as saying.
</P>
<P>
Distillate stocks grew last week by 1.5 million barrels as the
key market for heating oil in the northeast U.S. basked in
unseasonably warm temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the market in the long term would pay little
attention to the API report as disappointment with last week's
OPEC's meeting in Vienna would linger.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said oil prices in the single digits were not
unforseeable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
